1
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,640
I've been thinking day and night.

2
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:34,960
I've been wondering

3
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:36,240
why people

4
00:01:36,240 --> 00:01:38,520
keep buying clothes non-stop.

5
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:41,360
In the past, people wore clothes

6
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:42,680
to cover themselves

7
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:44,080
and keep warm.

8
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:47,080
But why now

9
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:48,440
do they still constantly go shopping

10
00:01:48,440 --> 00:01:49,240
for clothes?

11
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,320
Why is that?

12
00:01:51,759 --> 00:01:52,640
Fashion.

13
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:54,200
So my store

14
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:56,120
isn't just a clothing store.

15
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:58,120
It's also a fashion boutique.

16
00:01:58,560 --> 00:01:59,320
Look.

17
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:00,520
Fashion,

18
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:02,120
it covers a wide range.

19
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:03,320
For example,

20
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:06,050
the fashion in the Qing Dynasty

21
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:08,639
was long robes, mandarin jackets,

22
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:09,880
and qipaos.

23
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:11,560
A decade or so ago,

24
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,520
our fashion

25
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:14,560
was pure wool Zhongshan suits

26
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:16,120
and Dacron pants.

27
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:17,880
As time changes,

28
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:20,000
fashion is also being redefined.

29
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,880
Fashion also varies between different regions.

30
00:02:23,880 --> 00:02:24,610
For example,

31
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:26,240
Italian fashion

32
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:28,640
might be completely incomprehensible to Africans.

33
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:29,520
So,

34
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:31,120
I've been researching

35
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:34,060
what constitutes fashion for us Northeasterners.

36
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:36,200
What is this Northeastern fashion?

37
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:37,640
My research shows that

38
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:40,240
we Northeasterners like bright things,

39
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:41,520
flashy things.

40
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:43,079
Like what you're wearing.

41
00:02:43,079 --> 00:02:44,340
That's pretty much it.

42
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,079
Why?

43
00:02:46,440 --> 00:02:47,200
Because

44
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,880
during those winter months

45
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:50,410
when it snows heavily here,

46
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:51,800
once it snows,

47
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:54,320
the entire city turns white.

48
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:56,560
If you dress brightly

49
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:57,760
and flashily,

50
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:59,320
in the snow,

51
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,930
you're easy to find and won't get lost.

52
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,760
Anti-kidnapping?

53
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,640
You could say that.

54
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:08,000
So...

55
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,800
Do you know Versace?

56
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:13,440
That guy who sells buns next door to me?

57
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:14,520
That's Fan Siwei.

58
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:15,960
Must be his cousin

59
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:17,120
all with the same generation name, huh?

60
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:18,640
Versace sells clothes.

61
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:19,440
A tailor?

62
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,079
An Italian tailor.

63
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:23,000
Turn around and look,

64
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,079
that's his work.

65
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:25,960
You know what,

66
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:27,400
these Italians really have a style.

67
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:29,060
That yellow shirt over there.

68
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:32,200
He made this?

69
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:33,760
Is it bright?

70
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:34,520
Yes, it is.

71
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,800
Like a little leopard coming down the mountain.

72
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:37,640
Do you like it?

73
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:39,329
Take it. It's yours.

74
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:40,880
No, why give me

75
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:41,640
such an expensive gift?

76
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:42,440
Put it on.

77
00:03:43,079 --> 00:03:45,740
Wear it every day. Once you understand Versace,

78
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:46,760
you'll grasp

79
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:48,690
the soul of Northeastern fashion.

80
00:03:48,760 --> 00:03:50,120
I'd rather not, brother.

81
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:51,880
I'm just a kebab seller.

82
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:53,880
If I wore this, people would die laughing.

83
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:54,760
You don't like dressing up, right?

84
00:03:54,760 --> 00:03:55,560
Right.

85
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:56,880
I've studied this too.

86
00:03:56,880 --> 00:03:58,760
Why most men

87
00:03:58,760 --> 00:03:59,760
don't like dressing up,

88
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:00,960
while most women

89
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:02,000
love to dress up

90
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,440
and shop so much?

91
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,880
It's because

92
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:09,000
our genes are at work.

93
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:11,120
How so?

94
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,440
Look, in primitive society,

95
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:14,320
we men had to go hunting.

96
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,320
And women?

97
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:17,640
They just carried little baskets,

98
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,000
picking wild fruits

99
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,240
and gathering mushrooms.

100
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,840
So they have it in their genes

101
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:24,580
to enjoy browsing around.

102
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:25,880
That's why in my store,

103
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:28,010
95% of the items are women's clothing.

104
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:29,080
This is also

105
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:30,970
the secret to making money.

106
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:31,640
Oh, brother!

107
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:33,560
I'm feeling a bit dazed here.

108
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:35,440
If you stand by this counter

109
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:36,880
with your hand like this and the spotlight on

110
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:38,200
you'll have that cool vibe, bro.

111
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,560
You're really something.

112
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:40,520
When do you think I'll be able

113
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:41,240
to be like you

114
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,320
and run my barbecue business

115
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:44,000
as thoroughly as you do?

116
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:45,400
Come see me whenever you're free.

117
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:46,860
We should chat more often.

118
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:48,400
Actually, I came today

119
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:50,000
mainly to say goodbye.

120
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,560
I'm closing my barbecue shop.

121
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,440
What happened?

122
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:54,300
Because of you.

123
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:55,800
You taught me to dig deeper.

124
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,560
I hung a map on my wall.

125
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:58,880
Every day I studied it

126
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:00,320
wondering where to open a new barbecue shop.

127
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:01,760
Finally, I reached a conclusion:

128
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:03,440
Dongguan, Guangdong.

129
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:06,120
Why go there?

130
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:07,440
I've done my research.

131
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:08,320
That place has

132
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:09,880
many Taiwanese and Hong Kong companies

133
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:11,560
operating there.

134
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,120
The key is that many

135
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,760
of our fellow Northeasterners work there.

136
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:16,320
When they get homesick

137
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:17,960
I'll show up and get to work

138
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:18,760
grilling some skewers for them.

139
00:05:18,760 --> 00:05:19,760
Once they eat and feel happy

140
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:20,960
they'll bring friends from Hunan

141
00:05:20,960 --> 00:05:21,640
and Jiangxi

142
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:22,880
and workers from all over China will come to eat.

143
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:24,880
How could this business not boom?

144
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:27,420
That's not bad.

145
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:28,920
Interesting.

146
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,530
I've learned a bit from you.

147
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:32,560
Don't mention it.

148
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:33,520
Good luck.

149
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:34,760
I came today

150
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:36,400
just to say goodbye to you, bro.

151
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,560
It's good to see you one more time.

152
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,560
Well, I...

153
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:42,760
Gotta go.

154
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,320
Do well.

155
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:48,400
Wait.

156
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,450
Take that shirt with you

157
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:53,000
and wear it in Guangdong.

158
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,120
Don't let down

159
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:56,760
the reputation of us Northeasterners.

160
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:59,360
Grilling barbecue in Versace, how about that?

161
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:15,000
Just return the hanger to me.

162
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,240
Guess how much we made in the first month?

163
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,000
How much?

164
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,120
23,000.

165
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:32,780
That's several years of our previous salaries.

166
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:35,880
We'll be able to buy a Santana soon.

167
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:39,450
Then I'll drive the Santana

168
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:41,400
to Mengmeng's grandfather's house,

169
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:42,880
and right in front of Mengmeng,

170
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:44,520
I'll slam

171
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:45,520
the car keys on the table

172
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:46,760
and let her mock me.

173
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:48,700
Your own daughter humiliates you

174
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,300
and ridicules you.

175
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:51,360
Shouldn't you

176
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,560
reflect on yourself?

177
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,720
In less than a year,

178
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:56,050
we'll buy that Santana.

179
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,120
Then you need to

180
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,760
stop causing trouble for a year.

181
00:06:58,760 --> 00:07:00,760
Will you get your lawyer's license?

182
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:03,160
That incident with Xiaokong Glasses,

183
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:04,760
it created a bad public impression.

184
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:05,360
They now think

185
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,760
there's something wrong with my character.

186
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:07,640
I guess the lawyer's license

187
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:09,240
won't be issued to me for now.

188
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:10,800
What about in the future?

189
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,330
They won't give it to me either.

190
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:15,000
Actually,

191
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,240
it doesn't matter whether you get that license or not.

192
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:18,240
Aren't you doing well now?

193
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,520
The business is running,

194
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:21,650
as long as our family is safe and sound.

195
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,960
I don't necessarily need to be a lawyer.

196
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:26,010
But this matter with Guo Dapao,

197
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:27,660
what can we do about it?

198
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,240
Guo Dapao is fine,

199
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:31,240
but his daughter is so pitiful.

200
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:32,640
She's so young. What should we do?

201
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:33,840
Yes, what do you think

202
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:34,880
we should do?

203
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:36,260
It's worrying.

204
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:40,159
Should we save some of the money?

205
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:42,520
Bring me that thick stack.

206
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:43,850
I want to count it again.

207
00:07:44,520 --> 00:07:46,280
I'll give you some money to burn.

208
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:47,000
Come on, let's race.

209
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,200
Let's race together.

210
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:49,640
Ready,

211
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:50,159
go!

212
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:15,880
You opened it?

213
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:18,160
Is that a problem?

214
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:20,000
What kind of talk is this?

215
00:08:20,760 --> 00:08:21,880
Are you always this aggressive when you talk?

216
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:22,640
Even now,

217
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:24,120
as someone who's been around the block,

218
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,480
I don't talk like you do.

219
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:26,520
Yeah,

220
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:28,240
we've had a few scuffles before,

221
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:29,520
minor fights, right?

222
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:30,360
But I didn't come here today

223
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:32,000
looking for a fight.

224
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:33,440
So when you came in asking me

225
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:33,880
So when you first came in

226
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:34,120
if this was my shop

227
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,159
if I owned this place

228
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:36,039
What do you mean?

229
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:36,919
I don't own it.

230
00:08:36,919 --> 00:08:38,780
I just work here as a salesperson.

231
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:39,640
Now suddenly

232
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:40,919
I don't want to talk about anything else.

233
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:42,400
So what do you want to talk about?

234
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:44,360
There's something I'm really curious about.

235
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:46,400
What exactly do you do for a living?

236
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:47,760
Think about it.

237
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:49,120
Over the past year

238
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,120
we've only met

239
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,120
a few times.

240
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:53,040
Each time you have a different job.

241
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:53,720
At first you said

242
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:54,440
your job was

243
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:54,720
an engineer at a machinery factory.

244
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:56,050
A mechanical engineer.

245
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:57,480
But when I first met you

246
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,480
you were a singer.

247
00:08:58,880 --> 00:08:59,520
Right?

248
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:01,240
Then you set up a chess stall

249
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:02,280
in the park.

250
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:03,520
Now you're selling clothes.

251
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:04,280
What's going on?

252
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:05,600
I've had many jobs.

253
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:06,520
I've been a writer,

254
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:06,680
sold pinhole glasses,

255
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:07,640
sold vision therapy glasses,

256
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:08,720
and I'll do even more in the future.

257
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:09,760
Many more things.

258
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:11,520
Yeah, but what do you actually do?

259
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:13,040
You've got me completely confused.

260
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:14,120
Now I'm in fashion.

261
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:16,400
Aren't you selling clothes?

262
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:17,320
On the surface I sell clothes,

263
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:18,780
but really I'm in fashion.

264
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:24,120
Tell me the truth.

265
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:25,880
Are you

266
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:26,720
actually

267
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,000
a spy?

268
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:32,240
Why would you

269
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:33,640
think I'm a spy?

270
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:34,640
If you're not a spy,

271
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:35,400
why do you need

272
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,760
so many identities to cover yourself?

273
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:38,720
I'm just going to sell clothes from now on.

274
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:39,760
This year, next year,

275
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:42,240
the year after that. I'll keep selling clothes.

276
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,000
I see.

277
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:45,290
So you're going deep undercover, huh?

278
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:47,000
Let's just fight instead.

279
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,880
Talking to you is more exhausting than fighting.

280
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:50,810
You're not even my match in a fight.

281
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:52,280
Your brother-in-law would be more of a challenge.

282
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:52,920
Where is he?

283
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:53,760
Isn't he here?

284
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:55,480
Thanks to you, he's in jail.

285
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,400
What are you talking about?

286
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:58,120
In jail?

287
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:58,640
What happened?

288
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:00,160
You're being unreasonable now.

289
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:01,040
Look,

290
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:03,040
you brought him to fight me.

291
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:04,240
What was I supposed to do?

292
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:05,500
I had to defend myself.

